246
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:53,148
He just used to sit
next to me and cuddle.

247
00:34:53,224 --> 00:34:58,128
I was more of a mother to him
than that goddamned pig ever was.

248
00:34:58,196 --> 00:35:02,599
Don't talk like that about pigs.
They're usually nicer than people.

249
00:35:02,667 --> 00:35:04,897
But they smell like shit.

250
00:35:06,838 --> 00:35:08,272
Not true.

251
00:35:08,340 --> 00:35:12,937
As a matter of fact,
right now I have one in my kitchen...

252
00:35:13,011 --> 00:35:14,911
that's very clean...

253
00:35:14,980 --> 00:35:19,110
- and smells very nice.
- You don't have a pig in your kitchen.

254
00:35:21,186 --> 00:35:22,620
Yes, I do.

255
00:35:22,687 --> 00:35:25,850
I was just in there,
and I didn't see any goddamned pig.

256
00:35:25,924 --> 00:35:29,360
Don't move.
I'll get him.

257
00:35:31,329 --> 00:35:33,263
Piggy, where are you?

258
00:35:34,866 --> 00:35:36,800
There you are.

259
00:35:43,875 --> 00:35:46,810
Hi, Mathilda.

260
00:35:46,878 --> 00:35:49,540
Hi, piggy.

261
00:35:57,022 --> 00:36:00,253
How are you today?

262
00:36:00,325 --> 00:36:02,885
I've seen better days.

263
00:36:10,001 --> 00:36:14,837
- What's your name?
- Leon.

264
00:36:17,208 --> 00:36:19,302
Cute name.

265
00:36:26,284 --> 00:36:30,380
You have anyone to go to,
any family anyplace else?

266
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:43,968
I'm gonna get some more milk.

267
00:37:02,620 --> 00:37:04,088
Holy shit.

268
00:37:10,128 --> 00:37:14,065
Don't touch that, please.

269
00:37:14,132 --> 00:37:16,533
What do you do for a living?

270
00:37:17,602 --> 00:37:19,070
Cleaner.

271
00:37:20,472 --> 00:37:22,406
You're a hit man?

272
00:37:26,077 --> 00:37:27,545
Cool.

273
00:37:40,125 --> 00:37:44,585
- Do you clean anyone?
- No women, no kids. That's the rules.

274
00:37:44,662 --> 00:37:47,723
How much would it cost to hire someone
to get those dirtbags...

275
00:37:47,799 --> 00:37:50,598
who killed my brother?

276
00:37:50,668 --> 00:37:54,434
- Five grand a head.
- Wow.

277
00:37:54,506 --> 00:37:58,602
How about I work for you...

278
00:37:58,676 --> 00:38:02,169
and in exchange,
you teach me how to clean?

279
00:38:02,247 --> 00:38:05,342
What do you think?

280
00:38:05,416 --> 00:38:07,441
I'll clean your place.
I'll do the shopping.

281
00:38:07,519 --> 00:38:09,749
I'll even wash your clothes.

282
00:38:11,022 --> 00:38:15,357
- Is it a deal?
- No, it's not a deal.

283
00:38:22,867 --> 00:38:27,703
What do you want me to do?
I've got no place to go.

284
00:38:27,772 --> 00:38:31,606
You've had a rough day today.

285
00:38:34,546 --> 00:38:37,038
Go to sleep,
and we'll see tomorrow.

286
00:38:51,496 --> 00:38:54,625
You've been really great
with me, Leon...

287
00:38:54,699 --> 00:38:57,725
and it's not always like that.

288
00:38:57,802 --> 00:38:59,668
You know?

289
00:39:07,378 --> 00:39:08,812
Good night.

290
00:40:25,189 --> 00:40:27,453
You sleep well?

291
00:40:27,525 --> 00:40:29,857
Good.

292
00:40:29,928 --> 00:40:32,363
- After breakfast you gotta take off.
- Where to?

293
00:40:32,430 --> 00:40:35,092
Not my problem.

294
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:50,915
Read it.

295
00:40:57,789 --> 00:40:59,814
You don't know how to read.

296
00:40:59,891 --> 00:41:02,883
I'm learning, but I've had
a lot of work lately...

297
00:41:02,961 --> 00:41:06,022
so I'm a little behind.

298
00:41:06,097 --> 00:41:07,565
What's it say?

299
00:41:07,632 --> 00:41:11,694
I've decided what to do with my life.
I wanna be a cleaner.

300
00:41:11,769 --> 00:41:16,229
You wanna be a cleaner.
Here.

301
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:21,074
Take it. It's a good-bye gift.
Go clean, but not with me.

302
00:41:21,145 --> 00:41:24,740
- I work alone. Understand?
- Bonnie and Clyde didn't work alone.

303
00:41:24,816 --> 00:41:27,808
Thelma and Louise didn't work alone.
They were the best.

304
00:41:29,988 --> 00:41:34,084
Mathilda, why are you
doing this to me?

305
00:41:34,158 --> 00:41:36,820
I've been nothing
but nice to you.

306
00:41:36,894 --> 00:41:39,761
I saved your life yesterday,
right outside the door.

307
00:41:39,831 --> 00:41:43,096
Right.
Now you're responsible for it.

308
00:41:43,167 --> 00:41:46,603
If you saved my life,
you must've saved it for a good reason.

309
00:41:46,671 --> 00:41:49,436
If you throw me out now,
it's like you never opened your door...

310
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:52,340
like you let me die
right there in front of it.

311
00:41:52,410 --> 00:41:57,814
But you did open it. So--

312
00:42:01,085 --> 00:42:05,454
If you don't help me,
I'll die tonight. I can feel it.

313
00:42:05,523 --> 00:42:07,787
I don't wanna die tonight.

314
00:42:10,328 --> 00:42:12,797
You're just a little girl.

315
00:42:12,864 --> 00:42:15,799
Don't take it badly,
but I don't think you could do it.

316
00:42:15,867 --> 00:42:17,301
I'm sorry.

317
00:42:36,054 --> 00:42:37,988
How's that?

318
00:43:11,923 --> 00:43:15,018
Don't you ever do that again
or I'll break your head.

319
00:43:15,093 --> 00:43:16,527
You got that?

320
00:43:17,762 --> 00:43:21,198
I don't work like that.
It's not professional.

321
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:23,199
There is rules.

322
00:43:24,268 --> 00:43:27,033
And stop saying "okay"
all the time!

323
00:43:30,108 --> 00:43:31,701
Good.

324
00:43:46,958 --> 00:43:49,188
You expect to use that
in this hotel?

325
00:43:51,162 --> 00:43:54,223
Mister, I have to use it...

326
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:58,394
because I have an audition
at Juilliard next month...

327
00:43:58,469 --> 00:44:00,699
and I have to practice.

328
00:44:00,771 --> 00:44:04,639
Okay, but not after 10:00.

329
00:44:04,709 --> 00:44:06,768
- I promise.
- All right.

330
00:44:08,779 --> 00:44:11,749
I'll put you
at the end of the hall...

331
00:44:11,816 --> 00:44:15,912
so that you
don't disturb anyone.

332
00:44:15,987 --> 00:44:17,477
Fill those out, please.

333
00:44:21,659 --> 00:44:26,654
Daddy, can I please fill them out?
I like to check in to hotels.

334
00:44:30,201 --> 00:44:32,397
Thanks, Pop.
I'll bring these back in a minute.

335
00:44:32,470 --> 00:44:34,734
Fourth floor!

336
00:44:34,805 --> 00:44:36,398
Thanks, mister!

337
00:44:36,474 --> 00:44:39,569
You're lucky to have a little girl
that's interested in things.

338
00:44:41,946 --> 00:44:45,405
I have a kid, 17,
does nothing all day long.

339
00:44:51,022 --> 00:44:54,083
Can I leave my plant here
while I take my stuff upstairs?

340
00:44:54,158 --> 00:44:55,956
Of course.

341
00:45:16,881 --> 00:45:20,146
I'm putting in a name of a girl
in my class who makes me sick.

342
00:45:22,687 --> 00:45:26,214
If things get hot,
she'll take the heat.

343
00:45:43,207 --> 00:45:45,835
There. Finished.

344
00:45:46,377 --> 00:45:49,369
- How old are you?
- Eighteen.

345
00:45:50,214 --> 00:45:53,206
- Eighteen?
- Want to see my license?

346
00:45:54,252 --> 00:45:58,519
No. You just look a little young.

347
00:45:59,290 --> 00:46:00,951
Thanks.

348
00:46:08,165 --> 00:46:11,726
Leon, I want you to teach me
how to be like you.

349
00:46:11,802 --> 00:46:14,066
I want to be strong and smart
like you.

350
00:46:15,840 --> 00:46:18,673
I know I'm not
strong enough yet...

351
00:46:18,743 --> 00:46:22,805
but I could learn the basics,
the theory.

352
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:27,010
What do you think?
Just the theory.

353
00:46:27,084 --> 00:46:29,348
I need this, Leon.

354
00:46:31,088 --> 00:46:33,182
I need time
to get my head together.

355
00:46:33,257 --> 00:46:36,022
Yeah, and I need...

356
00:46:41,766 --> 00:46:43,291
a drink.

357
00:46:43,367 --> 00:46:46,359
Don't move.
I'll go get one.

358
00:47:11,462 --> 00:47:14,898
When you told me
to get this baby out for you...

359
00:47:14,965 --> 00:47:17,229
I thought my hearin' was goin'.

360
00:47:17,301 --> 00:47:22,205
I says to myself, " Leon's a pro.
Nobody uses that except beginners."

361
00:47:22,273 --> 00:47:24,037
I like to stay in shape.

362
00:47:24,108 --> 00:47:28,568
Sure.
Always stay on top of it.

363
00:47:28,646 --> 00:47:32,344
It's like me. I gotta know
where everything is all the time.

364
00:47:32,416 --> 00:47:34,976
I never leave this place,
except to go from here to there.

365
00:47:38,389 --> 00:47:41,381
Change ain't good, Leon.
You know?

366
00:47:52,336 --> 00:47:53,770
Check it.

367
00:47:55,339 --> 00:47:58,001
- Make sure it's the right thing.
- I trust you.

368
00:47:58,075 --> 00:48:01,101
One thing's got nothin' to do
with the other. Remember that.

369
00:48:02,513 --> 00:48:04,447
I will.

370
00:48:19,497 --> 00:48:22,467
The rifle is the first weapon
you learn how to use...

371
00:48:22,533 --> 00:48:26,367
because it lets you
keep your distance from the client.

372
00:48:26,437 --> 00:48:28,667
The closer you get
to being a pro...

373
00:48:28,739 --> 00:48:31,936
the closer you can get
to the client.

374
00:48:32,009 --> 00:48:35,536
The knife, for example,
is the last thing you learn.

375
00:48:41,218 --> 00:48:42,652
Position.

376
00:49:06,811 --> 00:49:10,645
Never take it off until the last minute.
It reflects light.

377
00:49:10,714 --> 00:49:13,513
They can see you coming
from a mile away.

378
00:49:13,584 --> 00:49:17,316
And always dress down.

379
00:49:17,388 --> 00:49:20,517
Never brighter
than the floor, okay?

380
00:49:23,394 --> 00:49:28,025
Let's practice now.
It's the best way to learn.

381
00:49:28,098 --> 00:49:30,192
Who should I hit?

382
00:49:30,267 --> 00:49:31,860
Whoever.

383
00:49:38,776 --> 00:49:41,040
I'll be with you in a second.
Give me a few minutes. Thank you.

384
00:49:41,111 --> 00:49:43,876
You guys get lost.
I don't want to see you.

385
00:49:43,948 --> 00:49:47,407
- Is everyone in position?
- This has to look natural.

386
00:49:56,961 --> 00:50:00,397
- No women, no kids. Right?
- Right.

387
00:50:07,671 --> 00:50:10,072
Jogger in the yellow and orange?

388
00:50:14,645 --> 00:50:17,046
Keep calm.

389
00:50:20,317 --> 00:50:23,878
Don't take your eyes off him.

390
00:50:23,954 --> 00:50:25,752
Breathe easy.

391
00:50:27,491 --> 00:50:29,118
Watch his movement.

392
00:50:31,662 --> 00:50:34,097
Pretend you're running with him.

393
00:50:37,134 --> 00:50:40,263
Try to feel his next movement.

394
00:50:41,839 --> 00:50:45,173
Take a deep breath.
Hold it.

395
00:50:53,751 --> 00:50:55,219
Now.

396
00:50:55,286 --> 00:50:57,118
Oh, my God!

397
00:50:57,187 --> 00:51:00,885
- I'm all right. I'm fine.
- Get down! Where'd that come from?

398
00:51:00,958 --> 00:51:04,724
One shot. Not bad, huh?

399
00:51:04,795 --> 00:51:07,230
- Who the hell fired?
- I just can't breathe! Get off me.

400
00:51:07,298 --> 00:51:10,962
Can we try
with real bullets now?

401
00:51:11,035 --> 00:51:13,003
Not today.
Let's pack up.

402
00:51:22,379 --> 00:51:23,813
Like that.

403
00:52:06,190 --> 00:52:09,524
- No, thanks.
- No discussion.

404
00:52:51,268 --> 00:52:53,236
" It seemed...

405
00:52:54,638 --> 00:52:56,572
to Socrates--',

406
00:53:04,381 --> 00:53:06,315
I'll do it.

407
00:53:20,330 --> 00:53:22,822
Leon, all we do is work.

408
00:53:22,900 --> 00:53:26,029
We need a break.
Let's play a game.

409
00:53:26,103 --> 00:53:29,767
- What kind of game?
- I have this great game.

410
00:53:29,840 --> 00:53:33,640
It makes you think and helps your
memory. It's exactly what you need.

411
00:53:47,024 --> 00:53:48,617
<i>Like a virgin</i>

412
00:53:50,494 --> 00:53:53,794
<i>Touched for the very first time</i>

413
00:53:58,268 --> 00:54:01,329
- Who is it?
- I don't know.

414
00:54:11,515 --> 00:54:17,284
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

415
00:54:17,354 --> 00:54:21,655
<i>Happy birthday, Mr. President</i>

416
00:54:21,725 --> 00:54:24,160
I don't know.

417
00:54:32,970 --> 00:54:34,802
Moustache.

418
00:54:38,809 --> 00:54:42,336
<i>I'm singing in the rain</i>

419
00:54:42,412 --> 00:54:45,006
<i>Just singing in the rain</i>

420
00:54:45,082 --> 00:54:47,642
<i>- What a beaut--</i>
- Gene Kelly?

421
00:54:49,253 --> 00:54:50,687
Good.

422
00:54:50,754 --> 00:54:53,587
Your turn now.

423
00:54:59,096 --> 00:55:00,860
Okay, pilgrim.

424
00:55:04,268 --> 00:55:05,736
Clint Eastwood?

425
00:55:12,609 --> 00:55:17,706
- I don't know. I give up.
-John Wayne.

426
00:55:17,781 --> 00:55:21,775
I was just about to say that.
I swear. It's amazing.

427
00:55:21,852 --> 00:55:24,219
Leon, really brilliant.

428
00:55:26,623 --> 00:55:28,557
Amazing.

429
00:55:43,473 --> 00:55:47,740
- You love your plant, don't you?
- It's my best friend.

430
00:55:47,811 --> 00:55:51,406
Always happy.
No questions.

431
00:55:52,983 --> 00:55:56,078
It's like me, you see.

432
00:55:56,153 --> 00:55:58,315
No roots.

433
00:55:58,388 --> 00:56:02,154
If you really love it, you should
plant it in a park so it can have roots.

434
00:56:06,230 --> 00:56:08,892
You should be watering me
if you want me to grow.

435
00:56:11,134 --> 00:56:12,568
You're right.

436
00:56:24,014 --> 00:56:25,448
Wait!

437
00:56:40,264 --> 00:56:44,861
They gotta be jumping out of the plate.
They gotta be alive.

438
00:56:52,943 --> 00:56:55,310
It's been a long time, Leon.

439
00:57:01,218 --> 00:57:03,186
I missed you.

440
00:57:03,253 --> 00:57:08,089
- And you missed some nice jobs too.
- Been training.

441
00:57:08,158 --> 00:57:12,152
Training's good,
but don't overdo it.

442
00:57:12,229 --> 00:57:14,630
Training don't pay
as good as working, Leon.

443
00:57:14,698 --> 00:57:16,166
Tony...

444
00:57:19,069 --> 00:57:23,700
all the money I make,
that you keep for me--

445
00:57:23,774 --> 00:57:25,765
You need some money?

446
00:57:25,842 --> 00:57:27,401
Just curious.

447
00:57:27,477 --> 00:57:29,411
I've been working
a long time...

448
00:57:29,479 --> 00:57:33,177
and I haven't done anything
with my money.

449
00:57:35,285 --> 00:57:41,088
I thought maybe
someday I could use it.

450
00:57:41,158 --> 00:57:43,525
You met a woman.

451
00:57:53,103 --> 00:57:55,197
You gotta be careful
with women.

452
00:57:55,272 --> 00:57:58,242
Remember when you arrived
in this country?

453
00:57:58,308 --> 00:58:02,711
When I took you in, you were still wet
behind the fuckin' ears...

454
00:58:02,779 --> 00:58:05,714
and, already, you were in deep shit
because of a woman.

455
00:58:05,782 --> 00:58:10,686
- Don't forget that, Leon.
- I wish I could sometimes.

456
00:58:13,290 --> 00:58:15,588
You know, about my money--

457
00:58:15,659 --> 00:58:20,062
Maybe I could give...

458
00:58:20,130 --> 00:58:22,224
a little...

459
00:58:23,767 --> 00:58:26,065
to someone.

460
00:58:26,136 --> 00:58:29,231
You know, to help out.

461
00:58:31,775 --> 00:58:35,803
It's your money. I'm just
holding it for you, like a bank.

462
00:58:35,879 --> 00:58:40,248
Except better than a bank
because banks always get knocked off.

463
00:58:40,317 --> 00:58:42,649
No one knocks off old Tony.

464
00:58:42,719 --> 00:58:45,245
Besides, with a bank...

465
00:58:45,322 --> 00:58:48,587
there's always tons of forms
and all that shit.

466
00:58:48,658 --> 00:58:53,755
But old Tony, nothin' to read,
nothin' to write. It's all in his head.

467
00:58:55,065 --> 00:58:58,399
I know how to read now.

468
00:58:58,468 --> 00:59:01,597
That's good, Leon.

469
00:59:04,508 --> 00:59:06,101
Your money's here.

470
00:59:06,176 --> 00:59:08,873
Whenever you want it,
you just ask me.

471
00:59:08,945 --> 00:59:13,007
- Here's a grand. Come on.
- It's okay. I don't need it.

472
00:59:13,083 --> 00:59:17,543
- Take it. Have some fun. Go ahead.
- Thank you.

473
00:59:17,621 --> 00:59:21,524
All right.
Now let's talk business.

474
00:59:21,591 --> 00:59:25,118
Don't move.
I'll go get the file.

475
00:59:25,195 --> 00:59:29,291
Manolo, a glass of milk
for my friend Leon here.

476
00:59:52,556 --> 00:59:54,991
Listen, Mathilda,
you better be careful.

477
00:59:55,058 --> 00:59:57,652
You can't just speak
to any guy off the street.

478
00:59:58,895 --> 01:00:01,660
Leon, get a grip.
What's the big fucking deal?

479
01:00:01,731 --> 01:00:04,496
I was just smoking a butt
while I was waiting.

480
01:00:06,236 --> 01:00:08,500
I want you to stop cursing.

481
01:00:08,572 --> 01:00:10,836
You can't talk to people
like that all the time.

482
01:00:10,907 --> 01:00:14,002
I want you to make an effort
to talk nice.

483
01:00:18,748 --> 01:00:21,979
And I want you to stop smoking.
It will kill you.

484
01:00:28,592 --> 01:00:31,357
Stay away from him.
He looks like a weirdo.

485
01:00:36,433 --> 01:00:40,199
I'll be out in five minutes.
Stand where I can see you.

486
01:00:53,617 --> 01:00:57,815
Leon, I think I'm kinda
falling in love with you.

487
01:01:00,390 --> 01:01:03,690
It's the first time for me,
you know.

488
01:01:03,760 --> 01:01:07,128
How do you know it's love
if you've never been in love before?

489
01:01:07,197 --> 01:01:10,064
'Cause I feel it.

490
01:01:10,133 --> 01:01:11,726
Where?

491
01:01:15,338 --> 01:01:17,272
In my stomach.

492
01:01:20,177 --> 01:01:23,636
It's all warm.

493
01:01:23,713 --> 01:01:28,947
I always had a knot there,
and now it's gone.

494
01:01:31,855 --> 01:01:37,123
Mathilda, I'm glad you
don't have a stomachache anymore.

495
01:01:37,194 --> 01:01:39,663
I don't think
it means anything.

496
01:01:39,729 --> 01:01:43,597
