02:03:15,421 --> 02:03:20,916
- Here's a hundred bucks to start.
- Can't I get a job instead?

996
02:03:20,994 --> 02:03:25,932
A job?
What the hell can you do?

997
02:03:25,999 --> 02:03:27,831
I can clean.

998
02:03:29,202 --> 02:03:31,671
I ain't got no work
for a 12-year-old kid...

999
02:03:31,738 --> 02:03:33,832
so get it out
of your goddamn head!

1000
02:03:33,907 --> 02:03:36,638
It's over!
The game's over!

1001
02:03:36,709 --> 02:03:39,440
Leon's dead!

1002
02:03:39,512 --> 02:03:41,480
You hear me?

1003
02:03:48,688 --> 02:03:53,421
Come on. You think
I ain't hurtin' too?

1004
02:03:58,898 --> 02:04:01,299
But he's dead.

1005
02:04:01,367 --> 02:04:05,326
You're gonna forget all this craziness
and get your little ass back to school.

1006
02:04:06,572 --> 02:04:09,667
Now take this money
and get the hell outta here.

1007
02:04:09,742 --> 02:04:11,836
Don't let me see your face
till next month...

1008
02:04:11,911 --> 02:04:16,178
'cause something tells me
I'm about to lose my famous kind streak.

1009
02:05:07,433 --> 02:05:10,892
My parents...

1010
02:05:10,970 --> 02:05:13,064
died...

1011
02:05:13,139 --> 02:05:17,736
in a car accident
four weeks ago.

1012
02:05:17,810 --> 02:05:19,744
It was terrible.

1013
02:05:22,315 --> 02:05:26,081
We didn't have the time to get to know
one another when you first came here...

1014
02:05:26,152 --> 02:05:30,885
but I want you to know I'm not the kind
of woman who'd let down a child...

1015
02:05:30,957 --> 02:05:34,291
whatever her situation,
whatever her mistake.

1016
02:05:34,360 --> 02:05:39,423
So I'm going to help you and do my best
to welcome you here again.

1017
02:05:41,334 --> 02:05:43,996
But on one condition:

1018
02:05:44,070 --> 02:05:47,267
You have to stop lying to me,
Mathilda.

1019
02:05:47,340 --> 02:05:49,502
I want you to take a chance...

1020
02:05:49,575 --> 02:05:52,510
and trust me.

1021
02:05:52,578 --> 02:05:55,104
Tell me what happened to you.

1022
02:05:58,518 --> 02:06:01,613
My family got shot down
by D.E.A. officers...

1023
02:06:01,687 --> 02:06:05,123
because of a drug problem.

1024
02:06:05,191 --> 02:06:07,785
I left with the greatest guy on Earth.

1025
02:06:07,860 --> 02:06:12,627
He was a hit man, the best in town,
but he died this morning.

1026
02:06:12,698 --> 02:06:16,566
If you don't help me,
I'll be dead by tonight.

1027
02:06:35,955 --> 02:06:39,619
- You know her?
- I've never seen her.

1028
02:07:06,185 --> 02:07:08,847
I think we'll be okay here.

